From bfba753e663ad8d15f1289d9fcea1b5d91f93f08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 17:55:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] netlink: name NETLINK_KEY and NETLINK_L2FLOW in cb_mutex
 string table
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The nlk_cb_mutex_key_strings[] array is declared sized [MAX_LINKS + 1]
(65 entries with MAX_LINKS=64) but only initialized for indices 0..32,
with a "nlk_cb_mutex-MAX_LINKS" sentinel placed at index 32 — left over
from when MAX_LINKS actually was 32. Indices 33..64 are implicitly NULL.

Since NETLINK_L2FLOW = 33 (added by the ASK patch bundle), creating a
kernel netlink socket on that protocol hands lockdep a NULL name:

    WARNING at lockdep.c:4925 DEBUG_LOCKS_WARN_ON(!name)
    lockdep_init_map_type
    __netlink_create
    __netlink_kernel_create
    abm_init [auto_bridge]

Also, the sentinel at index 32 misnames NETLINK_KEY = 32 as "MAX_LINKS"
on every boot. Swap that entry to the real name and add an L2FLOW entry
at index 33.

This only affects lockdep trace readability and the DEBUG_LOCKS_WARN_ON
above — no functional change.

Signed-off-by: Tomaz Zaman <tomaz@mono.si>
---
 net/netlink/af_netlink.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/netlink/af_netlink.c b/net/netlink/af_netlink.c
index 8b060465a2be..5fa41e9e22da 100644
--- a/net/netlink/af_netlink.c
+++ b/net/netlink/af_netlink.c
@@ -127,6 +127,8 @@ static const char *const nlk_cb_mutex_key_strings[MAX_LINKS + 1] = {
 	"nlk_cb_mutex-29",
 	"nlk_cb_mutex-30",
 	"nlk_cb_mutex-31",
+	"nlk_cb_mutex-KEY",        /* NETLINK_KEY = 32 */
+	"nlk_cb_mutex-L2FLOW",     /* NETLINK_L2FLOW = 33 (ASK) */
 	"nlk_cb_mutex-MAX_LINKS"
 };
 
-- 
